#: src/config.md:5
msgid ""
"You can configure maturin in `tool.maturin` section of [`pyproject.toml`]"
"(https://packaging.python.org/en/latest/specifications/pyproject-toml/"
"#arbitrary-tool-configuration-the-tool-table)."
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:7
msgid "Configuration keys"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:9
msgid "Cargo options"
msgstr "Cargo 選項"

#: src/config.md:11
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[tool.maturin]\n"
"# Build artifacts with the specified Cargo profile\n"
"profile = \"release\"\n"
"# For \"editable\" builds, use the specified Cargo profile,\n"
"# e.g. to use \"dev\" builds for local development\n"
"# (uses `profile` if this key is not set)\n"
"editable-profile = \"release\"\n"
"# List of features to activate\n"
"features = [\"foo\", \"bar\"]\n"
"# Features can also be conditional on the target Python version\n"
"# using PEP 440 version specifiers:\n"
"# features = [\n"
"#   \"always-on-feature\",\n"
"#   { feature = \"pyo3/abi3-py311\", python-version = \">=3.11\" },\n"
"#   { feature = \"pyo3/abi3-py38\", python-version = \"<3.11\" },\n"
"# ]\n"
"# Activate all available features\n"
"all-features = false\n"
"# Do not activate the `default` feature\n"
"no-default-features = false\n"
"# Cargo manifest path\n"
"manifest-path = \"Cargo.toml\"\n"
"# Require Cargo.lock and cache are up to date\n"
"frozen = false\n"
"# Require Cargo.lock is up to date\n"
"locked = false\n"
"# Override a configuration value (unstable)\n"
"config = []\n"
"# Unstable (nightly-only) flags to Cargo, see 'cargo -Z help' for details\n"
"unstable-flags = []\n"
"# Extra arguments that will be passed to rustc as `cargo rustc [...] -- "
"[...] [arg1] [arg2]`\n"
"rustc-args = []\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:46
msgid ""
"These are `cargo` build options, refer Cargo documentation [here](https://"
"doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/commands/cargo-rustc.html)."
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:48
msgid "maturin options"
msgstr "maturin 選項"

#: src/config.md:50
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[tool.maturin]\n"
"# Include additional files\n"
"include = []\n"
"# Exclude files\n"
"exclude = []\n"
"# Bindings type\n"
"bindings = \"pyo3\"\n"
"# Control the platform tag and PyPI compatibility\n"
"compatibility = \"pypi\"\n"
"# auditwheel mode, possible values are repair, check and skip\n"
"auditwheel = \"repair\"\n"
"# Don't check for manylinux compliance, deprecated in favor of auditwheel = "
"\"skip\"\n"
"skip-auditwheel = false\n"
"# Python source directory\n"
"python-source = \"src\"\n"
"# Python packages to include\n"
"python-packages = [\"foo\", \"bar\"]\n"
"# Strip the library for minimum file size\n"
"strip = true\n"
"# Source distribution generator,\n"
"# supports cargo (default) and git.\n"
"sdist-generator = \"cargo\"\n"
"# Include the Windows import library (.dll.lib or .dll.a) in the wheel.\n"
"# This is useful when distributing shared libraries that other programs\n"
"# need to link against at compile time.\n"
"include-import-lib = false\n"
"# Use base Python executable instead of venv Python executable in PEP 517 "
"build.\n"
"#\n"
"# This can help avoid unnecessary rebuilds, as the Python executable does "
"not change\n"
"# every time. It should not be set when the sdist build requires packages "
"installed\n"
"# in venv. This can also be set with the `MATURIN_PEP517_USE_BASE_PYTHON` "
"environment\n"
"# variable.\n"
"use-base-python = false\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:86
msgid ""
"The `[tool.maturin.include]` and `[tool.maturin.exclude]` configuration are "
"inspired by [Poetry](https://python-poetry.org/docs/pyproject/#exclude-and-"
"include)."
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:90
msgid ""
"Glob patterns are resolved relative to the directory containing `pyproject."
"toml`. When using `python-source` (e.g. `python-source = \"src/python\"`), "
"patterns are also tried relative to the `python-source` directory if they "
"don't match relative to `pyproject.toml`. This means you can use a single "
"pattern like `include = [\"mypackage/data.txt\"]` and it will work for both "
"sdist and wheel targets: the sdist will include the file at its original "
"location (`src/python/mypackage/data.txt`), and the wheel will include it at "
"the package-relative path (`mypackage/data.txt`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:99
msgid "To specify files or globs directly:"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:101
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"include = [\"path/**/*\", \"some/other/file\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"include = [\"path/**/*\", \"some/other/file\"]\n"
"```"

#: src/config.md:105
msgid "To specify a specific target format (`sdist` or `wheel`):"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:107
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"include = [\n"
"  { path = \"path/**/*\", format = \"sdist\" },\n"
"  { path = \"all\", format = [\"sdist\", \"wheel\"] },\n"
"  { path = \"for/wheel/**/*\", format = \"wheel\" }\n"
"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"include = [\n"
"  { path = \"path/**/*\", format = \"sdist\" },\n"
"  { path = \"all\", format = [\"sdist\", \"wheel\"] },\n"
"  { path = \"for/wheel/**/*\", format = \"wheel\" }\n"
"]\n"
"```"

#: src/config.md:115
msgid ""
"The default behavior applies these configurations to both `sdist` and "
"`wheel` targets."
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:118
msgid ""
"To include files generated by a Cargo build script (`build.rs`) from the "
"crate's `OUT_DIR`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:121
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"include = [\n"
"  { path = \"cpu_features.json\", from = \"out-dir\", to = \"my_package/"
"\" },\n"
"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"include = [\n"
"  { path = \"cpu_features.json\", from = \"out-dir\", to = \"my_package/"
"\" },\n"
"]\n"
"```"

#: src/config.md:127
msgid ""
"The `path` is a glob pattern relative to `OUT_DIR`, and `to` specifies the "
"target directory inside the wheel. This only applies to wheel builds (not "
"sdist), since `OUT_DIR` does not exist until `cargo build` runs."
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:131
msgid ""
"To include files from a different workspace member's `OUT_DIR`, specify the "
"crate name:"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:134
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"include = [\n"
"  { path = \"generated/*.py\", from = \"out-dir\", to = \"my_package/\", "
"crate-name = \"my-other-crate\" },\n"
"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"include = [\n"
"  { path = \"generated/*.py\", from = \"out-dir\", to = \"my_package/\", "
"crate-name = \"my-other-crate\" },\n"
"]\n"
"```"

#: src/config.md:140
msgid "SBOM options"
msgstr "SBOM 選項"

#: src/config.md:142
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[tool.maturin.sbom]\n"
"# Generate a CycloneDX SBOM for the Rust dependency tree.\n"
"# Defaults to true when the sbom feature is enabled.\n"
"rust = true\n"
"# Generate a CycloneDX SBOM for external shared libraries grafted during\n"
"# auditwheel repair. Defaults to true when repair copies libraries.\n"
"auditwheel = true\n"
"# Additional SBOM files to include in the wheel.\n"
"# Paths are relative to the project root.\n"
"include = [\"sboms/vendor.cdx.json\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:155
msgid "See the [SBOM](./sbom.md) page for more details."
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:157
msgid "target specific maturin options"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:159
msgid ""
"Currently only macOS deployment target SDK version can be configured for "
"`x86_64-apple-darwin` and `aarch64-apple-darwin` targets, other targets have "
"no options yet."
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:163
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[tool.maturin.target.<triple>]\n"
"# macOS deployment target SDK version\n"
