#: src/index.md:202
msgid "Python metadata"
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:204
msgid ""
"maturin supports [PEP 621](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0621/), you "
"can specify python package metadata in `pyproject.toml`. maturin merges "
"metadata from `Cargo.toml` and `pyproject.toml`, `pyproject.toml` takes "
"precedence over `Cargo.toml`."
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:207
msgid ""
"To specify python dependencies, add a list `dependencies` in a `[project]` "
"section in the `pyproject.toml`. This list is equivalent to "
"`install_requires` in setuptools:"
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:209
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[project]\n"
"name = \"my-project\"\n"
"dependencies = [\"flask~=1.1.0\", \"toml>=0.10.2,<0.11.0\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[project]\n"
"name = \"my-project\"\n"
"dependencies = [\"flask~=1.1.0\", \"toml>=0.10.2,<0.11.0\"]\n"
"```"

#: src/index.md:215
msgid ""
"You can add so called console scripts, which are shell commands that execute "
"some function in your program in the `[project.scripts]` section. The keys "
"are the script names while the values are the path to the function in the "
"format `some.module.path:class.function`, where the `class` part is "
"optional. The function is called with no arguments. Example:"
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:218
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[project.scripts]\n"
"get_42 = \"my_project:DummyClass.get_42\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[project.scripts]\n"
"get_42 = \"my_project:DummyClass.get_42\"\n"
"```"

#: src/index.md:223
msgid ""
"You can also specify [trove classifiers](https://pypi.org/classifiers/) in "
"your `pyproject.toml` under `project.classifiers`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:225
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[project]\n"
"name = \"my-project\"\n"
"classifiers = [\"Programming Language :: Python\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[project]\n"
"name = \"my-project\"\n"
"classifiers = [\"Programming Language :: Python\"]\n"
"```"

