#: src/metadata.md:59
msgid "Dynamic metadata"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:61
msgid ""
"Maturin has limited support for [dynamic metadata](https://packaging.python."
"org/en/latest/specifications/pyproject-toml/#dynamic) in `pyproject.toml`."
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:63
msgid ""
"When the `[project]` section is not present, maturin will populate metadata "
"from `Cargo.toml` with the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:65
msgid "`name` - From `package.name` in Cargo.toml"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:66
msgid ""
"`version` - From `package.version` in Cargo.toml (converted from SemVer to "
"PEP 440 format)"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:67
msgid "`summary` - From `package.description` in Cargo.toml"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:68
msgid ""
"`description` - From the contents of the README file specified in Cargo."
"toml's `package.readme`"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:69
msgid ""
"`description_content_type` - Set based on the README file extension (e.g. "
"`text/markdown` for `.md` files)"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:70
msgid "`keywords` - From `package.keywords` in Cargo.toml, joined with commas"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:71
msgid "`home_page` - From `package.homepage` in Cargo.toml"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:72
msgid "`author` - From `package.authors` in Cargo.toml, joined with commas"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:73
msgid ""
"`author_email` - From `package.authors` in Cargo.toml if it contains email "
"addresses"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:74
msgid "`license` - From `package.license` in Cargo.toml"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:75
msgid ""
"`project_url` - From various URLs in Cargo.toml (like repository, homepage, "
"etc.)"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:77
msgid ""
"When the `[project]` section is present in `pyproject.toml`, it must contain "
"at least the `name` field. Maturin will then merge metadata from `Cargo."
"toml` and `pyproject.toml`, `pyproject.toml` takes precedence over `Cargo."
"toml`. Per specification, maturin is not allowed to populate fields that are "
"not present in `project.dynamic` list when the `[project]` section is "
"present. For example, to use the Rust crate version as the Python package "
"version, you need to add `version` to the `project.dynamic` list. To use "
"`package.homepage` from `Cargo.toml`, add `urls` to `project.dynamic` and so "
"forth:"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:83
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[project]\n"
"name = \"my-awesome-project\"\n"
"dynamic = [\n"
"    \"version\",\n"
"    \"description\",\n"
"    \"readme\",\n"
"    \"urls\",\n"
"    \"authors\",\n"
"    \"license\",\n"
"    \"keywords\",\n"
"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[project]\n"
"name = \"my-awesome-project\"\n"
"dynamic = [\n"
"    \"version\",\n"
"    \"description\",\n"
"    \"readme\",\n"
"    \"urls\",\n"
"    \"authors\",\n"
"    \"license\",\n"
"    \"keywords\",\n"
"]\n"
"```"

#: src/metadata.md:97
msgid "Add Python dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: src/metadata.md:101
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[project]\n"
"name = \"my-project\"\n"
"dependencies = [\"flask~=1.1.0\", \"toml==0.10.0\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

